# Next.js app pages

## New product route

```
app/[locale]/{slug}/
  layout.tsx      # generateMetadata, robots if under construction
  page.tsx        # landing
  privacy/page.tsx
  terms/page.tsx
```

Mirror an existing app (e.g. `bit-scope/` full page, `zuli-collage/` under construction).

## Metadata

```typescript
import { buildCanonical, buildLanguageAlternates, getSiteUrl } from '@/lib/hreflang';

alternates: {
  canonical: buildCanonical(locale, '/my-app'),
  languages: buildLanguageAlternates('/my-app'),
}
```

Under construction: `robots: { index: false, follow: true }` via publish flag in layout.

## Store downloads

```tsx
<DownloadStoreFab
  appStoreUrl={t('download.appStoreUrl')}
  googlePlayUrl={t('download.googlePlayUrl')}
  utmContent="my-app"
/>
<StoreDownloadBadges ... utmContent="my-app" />
```

## Structured data

- `BreadcrumbsStructuredData` on every page
- `SoftwareApplicationStructuredData` on full product pages with store URLs
- Android ID in `lib/appStructuredData.ts` for JSON-LD

## Sitemap

Add routes in `app/sitemap.ts`. Legal pages always listed; main app path only when published.
